Former Gatanga Mp Peter Kenneth' s mother is dead. According to the family, Ms Rahab Wambui died at the Aga Khan Hospital in Nairobi on Thursday morning. Family sources said she had been at the Intensive Care Unit since November 2018 and had been confided to a wheelchair for the last 10 years. President Uhuru Kenyatta has send his condolences to Kenneth and the family following the dead of Mama Rahab. Through the State House tweet, Uhuru said that he was saddened by the death of Rahab. Secretary general of the United Nations Conference on Trade and Development Mukhisa Kituyi also shared a message of condolence to his friend Peter Kenneth “I share the pain of my friend Peter Kenneth on the demise of his dear mother, Rahab Wamboi. May you and family find the strength to bear this loss,”Kituyi said. More to follow...